✅ Fix 1: Run dmesg as root

You ran into a permissions issue. Try:

sudo dmesg | grep -i logitech


This will tell us if the kernel is autosuspending or throwing HID warnings.

✅ Fix 2: Disable USB Autosuspend for Logitech Receiver

Fedora sometimes autosuspends USB HID devices, causing mouse stutter. Create a udev rule:

sudo nano /etc/udev/rules.d/90-logitech-mouse.rules


Add:

ACTION=="add", SUBSYSTEM=="usb", ATTR{idVendor}=="046d", ATTR{idProduct}=="c542", TEST=="power/control", ATTR{power/control}="on"


Then reload:

sudo udevadm control --reload-rules
sudo udevadm trigger
